<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-18T02:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-18T02:25:00-05:00" n="475" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/207: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">George</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-18T10:00:00+02:35">March 18, 1935—10 a.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received March 18—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>26. My telegram No. 25.<note n="11" xml:id="d475fn11">Not
                                        printed.</note> Ethiopian delegation Paris instructed to
                                    appeal to Geneva under clause 15 of Pact.<note n="12" xml:id="d475fn12">Article 15 of the Covenant of the League
                                        of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Treaties, Conventions, etc.
                                            Between the United States of America and Other
                                            Powers</hi>, 1910–1923 (Washington, Government Printing
                                        Office, 1923), vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p.
                                        3336.</note> Ethiopian chiefs are joining their troops.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>